Date: 0/0/1927
Source: Natural History of Canterbury
Author: SPEIGHT
Vol / Page: 198
Edition:
Quote: <i>Mugiloidea</i>. An intermediate stage in the forward movement of the pelvic fins is represented in the little sea-mullet (<i>Agonostomus forsteri</i> (Plate I. fig. 2)), popularly known as "herring." It is a shore and estuarine form and feeds on the small shrimps which come in with the tide.
Notes: 1927 Archey `Native Fishes of Canterbury' in Speight et al. Natural History of Canterbury 198
